# waitForLoadState

Wait for page load states!

## Load States

```javascript
// Wait for document loaded
await page.waitForLoadState('load');

// Wait for DOM ready
await page.waitForLoadState('domcontentloaded');

// Wait for network idle
await page.waitForLoadState('networkidle');
```

> **Note:** In this sandbox, pages load almost instantly. In real applications, these commands wait for network activity and parsing to complete.

## Real World Scenario
When navigating to a Single Page Application (SPA), the standard "load" event might fire too early (before the app initializes). Waiting for `networkidle` ensures the initial data fetching is complete before you start interactions.

## Your Task
1. Navigate and wait for DOM ready
2. Get the page title

