# waitForFunction

Wait for custom conditions!

## Basic Usage

```javascript
await page.waitForFunction(() => window.myApp.isReady);
```

## With Arguments

```javascript
await page.waitForFunction(
    selector => document.querySelector(selector)?.textContent === 'Ready',
    '#status'
);
```

## DOM Condition

```javascript
await page.waitForFunction(() => {
    const items = document.querySelectorAll('.item');
    return items.length >= 5;
});
```

## Real World Scenario
Sometimes the wait condition is complex: "Wait until the video is at 50% progress" or "Wait until the canvas element has drawn the chart". `waitForFunction` gives you full power to execute logic right inside the browser page context.

## Your Task
1. Wait for counter to reach 3
2. Get the final value

